general_exclusion_criteria:
Unresolved Grade > 1 toxicities from prior anticancer therapy (except alopecia);
Recent palliative radiotherapy within 14 days or definitive radiotherapy within 42 days;
Concurrent participation in another investigational study;
History of severe hypersensitivity to study drugs or related compounds;
Inability to discontinue strong CYP3A4/5, CYP2C9, or CYP2C19 inhibitors/inducers or narrow‐index CYP3A4/5 substrates;
Inability to discontinue proton‑pump inhibitors;
Left ventricular ejection fraction below institution’s lower limits of normal;
Active uncontrolled medical illnesses;
Incapacity to ingest oral capsules intact;
New or progressing untreated brain metastasis or leptomeningeal disease likely needing imminent intervention;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Any prior treatment with a DNA‑protein kinase inhibitor.

