History of non‑infectious pneumonitis/interstitial lung disease requiring corticosteroids;
Active interstitial lung disease or unexplained pulmonary infiltrates suggestive of ILD at screening;
Lung‑specific acute severe comorbidities;
Unresolved active infection necessitating intravenous antimicrobial, antiviral, or antifungal therapy;
Pleural effusion, ascites or pericardial effusion requiring procedural drainage, catheter placement, or CART;
Medical disorders judged by investigator to compromise safe participation in the study.

