History of significant cardiac disease (New York Heart Association functional class higher than 2B);
Uncontrolled intercurrent medical illness;
Presence of a second active malignancy;
Severe sleep disorders such as narcolepsy;
Ophthalmologic conditions that prevent adequate light penetration (untreated cataract, severe glaucoma, macular degeneration, blindness, pupillary abnormalities, or other retinal disorders);
Severe psychiatric impairment (e.g., bipolar disorder or manic episodes);
Engagement in regular night‑shift work;
Prior utilization of light‑therapy interventions for fatigue or depression;
Recovery from ocular surgery within the preceding 6 months resulting in eye irritation;
Sensitivity to light, epilepsy, or personal history of seizures.

Hormone‑dependent cancers (breast, prostate, carcinoma of unknown origin);
Brain cancer;
Baseline hematocrit >48%;
Prostate‑specific antigen >4 ng/mL (Caucasian) or >3 ng/mL (African‑American);
First‑order relative with history of prostate cancer;
Uncontrolled congestive heart failure;
Severe untreated obstructive sleep apnoea;
Myocardial infarction, acute coronary syndrome, coronary revascularisation, or stroke within 3 months;
Previous stroke with residual cognitive or functional deficits or Mini‑Mental State Examination score <24;
Serum creatinine >2.5 mg/dL;
Alanine transaminase >3 times upper limit of normal;
Hemoglobin A1c >8.5%;
Body mass index >45 kg/m^2;
Untreated unipolar depression;
Bipolar disorder;
Schizophrenia.

