History of interstitial lung disease or pneumonitis;
Uncontrolled cardiovascular disease including New York Heart Association Class III‑IV heart failure;
Severe hepatic impairment (Child-Pugh C);
Renal impairment with estimated glomerular filtration rate <30 mL/min;
Untreated or progressive central nervous system involvement/metastasis;
Active infection with human immunodeficiency virus, hepatitis B virus, or hepatitis C virus;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Concurrent participation in another therapeutic oncology trial;
Any condition that, in the investigator’s judgment, would compromise participant safety or data integrity.

