Recurrent hepatoblastoma suitable for complete surgical resection (e.g., isolated pulmonary metastasis amenable to metastasectomy);
Pre-existing serious medical conditions such as heart failure, uncontrolled non‑cancer pulmonary disease, or severe psychiatric/social issues limiting compliance;
Active uncontrolled systemic bacterial, fungal, or viral infection;
Any active malignant disease other than the specified liver tumors;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Concurrent participation in other interventional studies or receipt of other investigational biologic, chemical, or radiologic therapies;
Known contraindication to conditioning chemotherapy agents fludarabine and cyclophosphamide;
Active autoimmune disease requiring systemic immunosuppression;
Significant venous occlusion compromising flow through the main portal vein, hepatic veins, or inferior/superior vena cava making the subject unsuitable;
History of solid-organ transplantation;
Tumor infiltration exceeding 50 percent of total liver volume.

