Known additional malignancy that progressed or required active treatment within the past two years;
Active central nervous system metastases or leptomeningeal disease;
Significant cardiovascular disease within six months preceding study drug initiation;
Ongoing systemic bacterial, fungal, or viral infection requiring treatment at baseline;
Confirmed chronic hepatitis B, hepatitis C, or HIV/AIDs infection;
Failure to resolve acute non‑hematologic toxicity from prior therapy to NCI‑CTCAE grade ≤1 before screening;
Active peripheral neuropathy of any grade at screening;
Uncontrolled diabetes mellitus;
Immunodeficiency or preexisting autoimmune disease deemed unsuitable for pembrolizumab;
History of non‑infectious pneumonitis or interstitial lung disease requiring corticosteroids or currently active pneumonitis/ILD;
Prior solid organ or bone‑marrow transplantation;
Prior high‑dose chemotherapy necessitating autologous stem‑cell rescue.

