History of clinically significant cardiovascular disease (recent MI, unstable angina, New York Heart Association class III‑IV heart failure);
Uncontrolled arterial hypertension;
Active serious infection including untreated HIV, chronic Hepatitis B or C;
Recent major surgery or trauma within 30 days;
Clinically meaningful interstitial lung disease, pneumonitis, or pulmonary fibrosis;
Severe hepatic impairment (Child‑Pugh Class C) or bilirubin > 3 mg/dL;
Renal insufficiency with estimated glomerular filtration rate <45 mL/min/1.73 m²;
Pregnancy, breastfeeding, or unwillingness to use effective contraception;
Performance status worse than ECOG 2 (unless already stipulated elsewhere).

