History of active non‑hematologic malignancies (with limited exceptions);
Pregnancy, lactation, or intention to conceive during study conduct;
Uncontrolled hypertension or symptomatic orthostatic hypotension;
Severe hepatic impairment (AST/ALT > 3× upper limit) or biliary obstruction;
Renal insufficiency (creatinine clearance < 30 ml/min);
Active Human Immunodeficiency Virus infection;
Untreated or inadequately treated hepatitis B or C infection;
Clinically significant autoimmune disorders;
Recent (within 3 months) acute coronary syndrome, unstable angina, or serious ventricular arrhythmias;
Left ventricular ejection fraction < 30%;
Severe valvular heart disease or congenital structural heart defects;
Prolonged QT interval (> 550 ms) absent pacing/device support;
Major surgical procedure requiring general anaesthesia within four weeks before enrollment;
New York Heart Association functional classification IV or acutely decompensated congestive heart failure;
Performance status worse than Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group 2/Karnofsky < 60%.

