Pregnancy at screening or becoming pregnant during the study;
Breastfeeding;
Uncontrolled intercurrent acute or chronic medical illness or psychiatric disturbance compromising safety or compliance;
Active uncontrolled central nervous system involvement (uncontrolled brain metastases);
Significant cardiac insufficiency (heart failure NYHA class III–IV);
Severe hepatic impairment (bilirubin ≥ 1.5× ULN) or marked hepatotoxic enzymes (AST/ALT ≥ 3× ULN);
Renal impairment (creatinine ≥ 1.5× ULN);
History of other active malignancies (“cancer survivor with evidence of active disease”).

Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Known hypersensitivity to study drugs, their metabolites, or formulation components;
History of myelodysplastic syndrome or acute myeloid leukemia, or diagnostic features suggesting these disorders;
Conditions impairing oral intake or causing malabsorption that would compromise drug delivery;
Previous allogenic solid organ or bone marrow transplantation (autologous HSCT also excludes);
Unresolved adverse events graded higher than CTCAE grade 1 attributable to prior anticancer therapy;
Active immunodeficiency or requirement for systemic glucocorticoids exceeding 10 mg/day prednisolone-equivalent;
Presence of an active secondary malignant neoplasm;
Documented untreated or actively progressing central nervous system metastasis, leptomeningeal disease, or primary CNS tumor;
Cardiac comorbidity meeting any of: myocardial infarction or unstable angina ≤6 months ago, clinically significant ventricular arrhythmia, high‑grade AV block, prolonged corrected QT > 470 ms, NYHA class III/IV heart failure, or left ventricular ejection fraction <40%;
Active serious infection necessitating antimicrobial therapy;
Chronic active hepatitis B infection (detectable HBV DNA), active hepatitis C infection (detectable HCV RNA), or HIV infection;
Past history of pneumonitis, interstitial lung disease, radiation‑induced pneumonitis, or any pulmonary toxicity requiring systemic steroids;
Symptomatic ascites or pleural effusions compromising respiratory function;
Concurrent medically or psychiatrically destabilising illnesses judged to interfere with study conduct;
Active ulcerative colitis or Crohn’s disease, or a history of intestinal obstruction or perforation within six months preceding registration;
Prior administration of topoisomerase 1 inhibitor‑based chemotherapy or topoisomerase 1 inhibitor‑containing antibody‑drug conjugates (applicable to combination cohorts);
Severe allergic or anaphylactic reactions to humanised monoclonal antibodies, IV immune globulin products, or related biological therapeutics.

