History of other malignancies except adequately treated non‑melanoma skin cancer, cured cervical intraepithelial neoplasia, or other solid tumours eradicated ≥3 years ago;
Known untreated or active brain or leptomeningeal metastases (stable treated CNS disease permissible under strict criteria);
Uncontrolled type 1 diabetes or inadequately controlled type 2 diabetes;
Clinically significant cardiovascular disease—including congestive heart failure NYHA class II or higher within six months, myocardial infarction within twelve months, unstable arrhythmias, uncontrolled hypertension (SBP ≥160 mmHg or DBP ≥100 mmHg), long QT/QTc >480 ms, or familial torsade predisposition;
Severe pulmonary disorders such as prior radiation‐induced pneumonitis or ongoing interstitial lung disease;
Significant hepatic impairment, renal insufficiency, or coagulopathy compromising safe administration of protocol therapy;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Concurrent participation in another interventional clinical trial.

Participants unable to give adequate informed consent;
Significant suicide risk (suicidal ideation with intent/plans within past six months);
History or current diagnosis of primary psychotic disorder, major depressive disorder with psychotic features, bipolar I disorder, or dissociative identity disorder;
Active substance use disorder within the past year;
Concurrent use of serotonergic antidepressants, SNRIs, TCAs, efavirenz, serotonin‐activating dietary supplements, MAO inhibitors, antipsychotics, mood stabilizers, aldehyde dehydrogenase inhibitors, strong UGT1A0/A1A10 inhibitors (cannot be safely tapered);
Unstable or clinically significant hematologic, endocrinologic, cerebrovascular, cardiovascular, coronary, pulmonary, renal, gastrointestinal, immune compromising, or neurologic diseases—including uncontrolled hypertension (>140/90 mm Hg), resting heart rate > 100 bpm, recent arrhythmias, prolonged QTc (>450 ms men, >460 ms women), myocardium infarction, coronary artery disease, heart failure, torsades de pointe risk factors;
Cirrhosis or liver failure;
Severe laboratory abnormalities grade ≥ 3 (CTCAE) affecting cognition or drug metabolism;
Brain tumors or untreated brain metastases;
Pregnant, breastfeeding, or potentially fertile women not employing acceptable contraceptive measures;
Known hypersensitivity to any component of psilocybin formulation.

history of another malignancy (except specified cured skin cancers, stage I melanoma, early‐stage prostate or breast cancer meeting cure intervals);
